RACE.RACE_TEXT: MEADOWLANDS RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 90. Claiming Purse 18180. (PLUS UP TO 40% NJB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 13. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 13 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $ 5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). (Rail at 17 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RESTORED ORDER vied two wide for the early lead, took over on the clubhouse turn, responded when challenged on the far turn, kicked clear at the top of the lane and held well under urging. MARKITOFF raced two wide off the pace, then three wide on the backside, bid three wide on the far turn, dug in gamely in the stretch run and held on for the place spot. DUBBY DUBBIE raced off the pace inside, chased inside on the far turn, rallied on the rail in the stretch drive and was outkicked for second. BIG RED ROCKS raced off the pace, chased inside on the far turn, rallied mildly on the rail, waited briefly for room at the sixteenth pole and then continued evenly. DREAM LINER (BRZ) raced off the pace, saved ground on the far turn, angled out and gained mildly between foes in the stretch run. MONARCHS GLEN (GB) raced two or three wide off the pace, came four wide into the lane and lacked a rally. UNLEVERAGED raced off the pace, moved up outside rivals nearing the far turn, chased three or four wide on the turn, then weakened. BIRD'S EYE VIEW raced two wide off the pace, then inside, came three wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. TIZ A PRINCE vied inside for the early lead, then tracked the winner, bid two wide on the far turn and faded. NANA FANNY did not factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SYNCOPATED raced off the pace between rivals, moved up inside on the far turn, rallied on the rail, angled out passing the furlong marker, closed steadily outside of DOOQ in deep stretch and was up in the final strides for the win. DOOQ dueled inside for the lead, dueled with PASCHAL MOON on the backside, shook free from that rival on the far turn, dug in gamely inside in the stretch run and yielded grudgingly late. TWO MINUTES APART was bumped at the start, tracked on the inside, moved up inside on the far turn, angled out, rallied outside in the stretch drive and was outkicked. BOOYAH raced three wide off the pace, chased on the far turn, came four wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. PASCHAL MOON dueled two wide for command, dueled on the backside, chased on the far turn and faded. SILVER SPRINTER was bumped at the start, steadied soon after, raced off the pace with an inside trip and did not factor. FIFTH ELEMENT was outrun.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEO MONTE set the pace on the inside while being pushed along, shook free midway on the backside, showed the way into the stretch, responded when roused, dug in gamely inside and held well late to prevail. HERE COMES BILLY stumbled at the start, bumped a rival and still broke on top, tracked the pace, chased inside on the far turn, angled out, rallied outside of LEO MONTE in the final furlong and dug in gamely to the finish.
